data.content:
Yes — MSTest v3+ supports **strongly-typed `DynamicData`**, eliminating the `object[]` boxing and giving you compile-time safety:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[DynamicData<string, bool>(nameof(TestData))]
public void Validate_ReturnsExpected(string input, bool expected)
{
    var result = Validator.IsValid(input);
    Assert.AreEqual(expected, result);
}

public static IEnumerable<(string, bool)> TestData =>
[
    ("valid@email.com", true),
    ("invalid", false),
    ("", false),
];
```

**What changed:**
- `DynamicData<string, bool>` — generic overload provides type safety
- Data returns `IEnumerable<(string, bool)>` tuples instead of `object[]`
- No more silent runtime failures from wrong types or argument count mismatches

Requires **MSTest v3.3+** (`MSTest.TestFramework` / `MSTest.Sdk`).
